---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import SectionHeader from '../../components/SectionHeader.astro';
import PullQuote from '../../components/PullQuote.astro';
import Annotation from '../../components/Annotation.astro';
---
<Base title="The One Question Test" section={3}>
  <SectionHeader n={3} title="The One Question Test" meta="~400w · interactive" />

  <div class="prose">

    <p>
      Here is a scalpel for every unnecessary dashboard panel: if you cannot name the
      specific decision this panel enables, remove it. Not "it helps us understand the
      business." The actual decision, the actual person, the actual moment.
    </p>

    <p>
      The test is brutal because most panels fail it immediately. Revenue trend?
      Someone might point at it during a board review. That is not a decision —
      that is narration. Active users this week? We check it every Monday. Still
      not a decision. Checking is not deciding. Monitoring is not acting.
    </p>

    <PullQuote>
      <p>If you can't name the specific decision this dashboard enables,
      it shouldn't exist. Not "it helps us understand the business" —
      the actual decision, the actual person, the actual moment.</p>
    </PullQuote>

    <p>
      A decision has three properties. It involves a choice between at least two paths.
      It is made by a specific person or group with the authority to act. And the data
      in question is actually capable of influencing which path is chosen. If your panel
      cannot satisfy all three, it is not enabling a decision. It is performing the
      idea of data-driven culture.
    </p>

    <p>
      The interactive below models this directly. Add the panels that live on your
      current dashboard. For each one, name the decision. If you leave the field blank —
      if you can't name one — the panel greys out. Watch how much of your dashboard
      disappears.
    </p>

  </div>

  <!-- Interactive: One Question Test -->
  <div class="interactive-sample warm" id="one-question-test">
    <div class="sample-chrome">One Question Test — Panel Builder</div>
    <div class="sample-body">
      <div class="oqt-layout">
        <div class="oqt-builder">
          <div class="oqt-input-row">
            <input
              type="text"
              id="panel-name-input"
              class="oqt-input"
              placeholder="Panel name (e.g. Weekly Active Users)"
              maxlength="60"
            />
            <input
              type="text"
              id="panel-decision-input"
              class="oqt-input oqt-input--decision"
              placeholder="Decision it enables (leave blank if none)"
              maxlength="100"
            />
            <button id="add-panel-btn" class="oqt-btn">Add panel</button>
          </div>
          <p class="oqt-hint">Try adding your real dashboard panels. Leave the decision blank to see what greys out.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="oqt-dashboard" id="oqt-dashboard">
          <!-- panels rendered here by JS -->
          <div class="oqt-empty-state" id="oqt-empty">
            <span>No panels yet — add one above</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="oqt-summary" id="oqt-summary" style="display:none">
          <span class="oqt-summary-live" id="oqt-live-count">0</span> of
          <span id="oqt-total-count">0</span> panels pass the test
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="prose">
    <Annotation label="Note">
      The test is not a reason to delete all your dashboards. It is a reason to be
      honest about which ones are doing work and which ones are doing performance.
      The ones that pass belong. The ones that fail are candidates for a different
      question: what decision would we need to make for this data to matter?
    </Annotation>
  </div>

</Base>

<style>
  .oqt-layout {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--sp-6);
  }

  .oqt-input-row {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--sp-2);
  }

  .oqt-input {
    background: var(--paper-0);
    border: 0.5px solid var(--paper-3);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    padding: var(--sp-2) var(--sp-3);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--ink-700);
    outline: none;
    transition: border-color var(--dur-fast) var(--ease-soft);
    width: 100%;
  }

  .oqt-input:focus {
    border-color: var(--terra-300);
  }

  .oqt-input--decision {
    border-color: var(--paper-2);
  }

  .oqt-btn {
    background: var(--terra-400);
    color: var(--paper-0);
    border: none;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    padding: var(--sp-2) var(--sp-4);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background var(--dur-fast) var(--ease-soft);
    align-self: flex-start;
  }

  .oqt-btn:hover { background: var(--terra-600); }

  .oqt-hint {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-caption);
    color: var(--ink-300);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .oqt-dashboard {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(160px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--sp-3);
    min-height: 80px;
  }

  .oqt-empty-state {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-caption);
    color: var(--ink-100);
    padding: var(--sp-6) 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  /* --- dynamically-rendered panel elements — must use :global() --- */
  :global(.oqt-panel) {
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: var(--sp-4);
    border: 1px solid;
    transition: opacity var(--dur-slow) var(--ease-soft),
                filter var(--dur-slow) var(--ease-soft),
                border-color var(--dur-slow) var(--ease-soft);
    position: relative;
  }

  :global(.oqt-panel--pass) {
    background: var(--paper-1);
    border-color: var(--terra-100);
  }

  :global(.oqt-panel--fail) {
    background: var(--paper-0);
    border-color: var(--paper-2);
    opacity: 0.35;
    filter: grayscale(1);
  }

  :global(.oqt-panel-name) {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-caption);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink-700);
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-1);
    white-space: nowrap;
    overflow: hidden;
    text-overflow: ellipsis;
  }

  :global(.oqt-panel--fail .oqt-panel-name) {
    color: var(--ink-300);
  }

  :global(.oqt-panel-decision) {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--terra-400);
    line-height: 1.4;
    display: -webkit-box;
    -webkit-line-clamp: 2;
    -webkit-box-orient: vertical;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  :global(.oqt-panel-nodecision) {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--ink-100);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  :global(.oqt-panel-remove) {
    position: absolute;
    top: 6px;
    right: 6px;
    background: none;
    border: none;
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--ink-100);
    cursor: pointer;
    padding: 2px 4px;
    border-radius: 3px;
    line-height: 1;
    transition: color var(--dur-fast);
  }

  :global(.oqt-panel-remove:hover) { color: var(--terra-400); }

  :global(.oqt-panel-mock-chart) {
    height: 28px;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-2);
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-end;
    gap: 3px;
  }

  :global(.oqt-bar) {
    flex: 1;
    border-radius: 2px 2px 0 0;
    background: var(--terra-100);
  }

  :global(.oqt-panel--fail .oqt-bar) {
    background: var(--paper-2);
  }

  .oqt-summary {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--ink-300);
    text-align: center;
    padding-top: var(--sp-2);
    border-top: var(--border-subtle);
  }

  .oqt-summary-live {
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--terra-600);
    font-size: var(--text-body);
  }
</style>

<script>
  const nameInput = document.getElementById('panel-name-input') as HTMLInputElement;
  const decisionInput = document.getElementById('panel-decision-input') as HTMLInputElement;
  const addBtn = document.getElementById('add-panel-btn') as HTMLButtonElement;
  const dashboard = document.getElementById('oqt-dashboard') as HTMLDivElement;
  const emptyState = document.getElementById('oqt-empty') as HTMLDivElement;
  const summaryEl = document.getElementById('oqt-summary') as HTMLDivElement;
  const liveCount = document.getElementById('oqt-live-count') as HTMLSpanElement;
  const totalCount = document.getElementById('oqt-total-count') as HTMLSpanElement;

  const panels: { name: string; decision: string }[] = [];

  // Seed with some realistic examples
  const seeds = [
    { name: 'Monthly Revenue', decision: 'Approve Q3 budget reforecast' },
    { name: 'Daily Active Users', decision: '' },
    { name: 'NPS Score', decision: '' },
    { name: 'Support Tickets Closed', decision: '' },
    { name: 'Churn Rate', decision: 'Trigger retention campaign threshold' },
    { name: 'Page Views', decision: '' },
  ];
  seeds.forEach(s => panels.push(s));

  const HEIGHTS = [14, 22, 18, 26, 20, 16, 24, 19];

  function renderBar(i: number) {
    return `<div class="oqt-bar" style="height:${HEIGHTS[i % HEIGHTS.length]}px"></div>`;
  }

  function render() {
    const passes = panels.filter(p => p.decision.trim().length > 0).length;

    // remove old panels (keep empty state node)
    Array.from(dashboard.children).forEach(c => {
      if (c !== emptyState) c.remove();
    });

    if (panels.length === 0) {
      emptyState.style.display = 'block';
      summaryEl.style.display = 'none';
      return;
    }

    emptyState.style.display = 'none';
    summaryEl.style.display = 'block';
    liveCount.textContent = String(passes);
    totalCount.textContent = String(panels.length);

    panels.forEach((p, idx) => {
      const pass = p.decision.trim().length > 0;
      const div = document.createElement('div');
      div.className = `oqt-panel ${pass ? 'oqt-panel--pass' : 'oqt-panel--fail'}`;
      div.innerHTML = `
        <button class="oqt-panel-remove" data-idx="${idx}" aria-label="Remove panel">×</button>
        <div class="oqt-panel-mock-chart">
          ${HEIGHTS.slice(0, 5).map((_, i) => `<div class="oqt-bar" style="height:${HEIGHTS[(idx * 3 + i) % HEIGHTS.length]}px"></div>`).join('')}
        </div>
        <div class="oqt-panel-name">${p.name}</div>
        ${pass
          ? `<div class="oqt-panel-decision">${p.decision}</div>`
          : `<div class="oqt-panel-nodecision">no decision named</div>`
        }
      `;
      dashboard.appendChild(div);
    });

    dashboard.querySelectorAll('.oqt-panel-remove').forEach(btn => {
      btn.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
        const idx = parseInt((e.currentTarget as HTMLElement).dataset.idx!);
        panels.splice(idx, 1);
        render();
      });
    });
  }

  addBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
    const name = nameInput.value.trim();
    if (!name) return;
    panels.push({ name, decision: decisionInput.value.trim() });
    nameInput.value = '';
    decisionInput.value = '';
    nameInput.focus();
    render();
  });

  [nameInput, decisionInput].forEach(el => {
    el.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
      if (e.key === 'Enter') addBtn.click();
    });
  });

  render();
</script>
